trans-unit.source: Represents an ordered collection of <xref href="System.Windows.Input.InputBinding"></xref> objects.
All objects that derive from <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> have an InputBindingCollection named <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.InputBindings%2A>.
All objects that derive from <xref:System.Windows.ContentElement> have an InputBindingCollection named <xref:System.Windows.ContentElement.InputBindings%2A>.

However, if these collections are set in [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)], then the items in the collection must be derived classes of <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> rather than direct <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> objects.
This is because <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> does not support a default public constructor.

Therefore, the items in a InputBindingCollection that was set in [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/add/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] will typically be an <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> derived class that does support a default public constructor, such as <xref:System.Windows.Input.KeyBinding> or <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding>.
